    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-09-04T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-09-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="1327"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1327">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 811.142/336f</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GJW2" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gerard</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">
                        <note n="1" xml:id="d1327fn1">The same, <hi rend="italic">mutatis
                                mutandis</hi>, to the Ambassadors in Great Britain, France, Russia,
                            and Austria-Hungary.</note>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-09-04">
                        <hi rend="italic">September 4, 1914</hi>.</date>
                </dateline>
                <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                <p>Department’s telegram of August 27 regarding Red Cross ship <hi rend="italic"
                        >Prinz Joachim</hi>. Department is informed that <persName>S. S. <hi
                            rend="italic">Hamburg</hi>
                    </persName> of Hamburg-American line has been chartered in place of <hi
                        rend="italic">Prinz Joachim</hi> and that the <hi rend="italic">Hamburg</hi>
                    will carry the name <hi rend="italic">Red Cross</hi>. In order to insure
                    neutrality of vessel authority has been given by special act of Congress for her
                    to sail under American flag. As <hi rend="italic">Hamburg</hi> is to sail for
                    European ports next Monday, bring matter again to attention of Foreign Office,
                    and obtain assurances at earliest moment that vessel will not be molested while
                    on voyage or in German ports. Also request Government to grant all courtesies
                    and waive formalities in order to facilitate issuance of clearance papers.
                    Report immediately.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BWJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
